<h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Patch 37 (October 21, 2014)</h4><ul><li>The diminishing return percentage for each additional stack of the Soul Master passive has been reduced to 0.5%, down from 1%.</li></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 31 (June 17th, 2014)</h4><ul><li>Fixed a bug where the first stack of Strife was granting double the amount of attributes as it should have been granting.</li></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 28.1 (April 24, 2014)</h4><ul><li>The initial bonus Power per stack of the Soul Master Unique Passive has been reduced to 0.25, down from 0.5.</li><li>The initial bonus Health per stack of the Soul Master Unique Passive has been reduced to 3, down from 4.</li></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 27 (March 17, 2014)</h4><ul><li>Fixed a bug where stacks on the Unique Passive Soul Collector would not correctly transfer upon upgrading to Strife.</li></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 26 (Feb 24, 2014)</h4><ul><li>Base Power reduced to 30, down from 42.</li><li>Base Health reduced to 250, down from 300</li><li>Price increased to 2630, up from 2560.</li><li>The Unique Passive - Soul Collector has been renamed to Soul Master.</li><li>Will carry the stacks of Soul Collector gained on the Advanced item Might when upgraded into Strife.</li></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 3 (June 21, 2013)</h4><ul><li>Updated the visual effect on this item.</li></ul>